quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  9,48,"Of old aimed they at sedition, and deranged thy affairs, until the truth arrived, and the behest of God became apparent, averse from it though they were"
  9,49,"Some of them say to thee, \"Allow me to remain at home, and expose me not to the trial.\" Have they not fallen into a trial already? But verily, Hell shall environ the Infidels"
  9,50,"If a success betide thee, it annoyeth them: but if a reverse betide thee, they say, \"We took our own measures before:\" and they turn their backs and are glad"
  9,51,"SAY: Nothing can befall us but what God hath destined for us. Our liege - lord is He; and on God let the faithful trust"
  9,52,"SAY: Await ye for us, other than one of the two best things? But we await for you the infliction of a chastisement by God, from himself, or at our hands. Wait ye then; we verily will wait with you"
  9,53,"SAY: Make ye your offerings willingly or by constraint; it cannot be accepted from you, because ye are a wicked people"
  9,54,"And nothing hindreth the acceptance of their offerings, but that they believe not in God and His Apostle, and discharge not the duty of prayer but with sluggishness, and make not offerings but with reluctance"